User_Message: What the f*** is PrEP, and why the hell should I care?
Response:
PrEP stands for pre-exposure prophylaxis. It is a medicine taken to prevent HIV. 

You might care because it can lower your chances of getting HIV if you are at risk. It is available as a daily pill or an injection every two months. 

If you have more questions or want to know how it works, feel free to ask!
